{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "e2aa6597-f893-446c-9bd6-13b4dc6fd94e",
    "name": "HayInsights OpenAPI (/openapi/v1)",
    "description": "Test collection for ALL HayInsights OpenAPI product endpoints (`/openapi/v1/*`).\n\n## Setup\n1. Set collection variable **`apiKey`** = your key (`apk_...`) — create one from the dashboard (Account → API keys).\n2. Set **`baseUrl`** (default `http://localhost:3000`; e.g. prod `https://api.hayinsights.com`).\n\n## Notes\n- Every request is API-key-only (rule S): the `X-API-Key` header is set at collection level and inherited.\n- Required query params are **enabled** (e.g. `economic-data?type`, `exchange-rate?currency1&currency2`, `etf compare codes`). Optional params are included but **disabled** — toggle them on as needed.\n- Access & quota follow your subscription plan. Response headers `X-RateLimit-*` show remaining quota.\n- Errors: 401 `API_KEY_REQUIRED`/`API_KEY_INVALID` · 403 `FEATURE_NOT_IN_PLAN` · 429 `RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED`.\n- All responses are wrapped in `{ success, statusCode, data, meta }`.\n",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "10633054"
  },
